# REAL-TIME-TRACKER

A real-time tracking application built using Node.js, Express.js, Socket.io, and Leaflet.

## Table of Contents
- [Introduction](#introduction)
- [Features](#features)
- [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)


## Introduction
The Real-Time Tracker is designed to provide real-time updates and tracking capabilities on a map. Whether you need to track live data streams, monitor real-time changes, or update users instantly, this application provides a robust foundation for such functionality.

## Features
- Real-time updates using WebSockets
- Interactive maps with real-time data
- Lightweight and fast
- Easy to integrate and extend
- Simple and intuitive UI

## Technologies Used
- **Node.js**: A JavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8 JavaScript engine.
- **Express.js**: A fast, unopinionated, minimalist web framework for Node.js.
- **Socket.io**: A JavaScript library for real-time web applications. It enables real-time, bidirectional, and event-based communication.
- **Leaflet**: An open-source JavaScript library for mobile-friendly interactive maps.

## Installation
To install and set up the project, follow these steps:

1. **Clone the repository**:
    ```sh
  git clone https://github.com/vamshicompililng/Realtime-tracker.git
    ```

2. **Navigate to the project directory**:
    ```sh
    cd realtime-tracker
    ```

3. **Install dependencies**:
    ```sh
    npm install
    ```

## Usage
To start the application, run:

```sh
npm start
